org.microbean.configuration.cdi.annotation

Annotation Type ConfigurationValue


  • @Documented
 @Qualifier
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={FIELD,METHOD,PARAMETER,TYPE})
public @interface ConfigurationValue
    A Qualifier annotation indicating that the annotated element is related to a particular configuration value in some way.

    In the case of method parameters and instance fields, this usually means that the annotated element would like to receive a particular configuration value from the MicroBean Configurations framework.

    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    ConfigurationCoordinate, Configuration

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Fields and Description
      static String NULL
      A String that stands in for null—annotation elements cannot be set to null so if either the value() or defaultValue() elements in this class return the value of this field it is to be interpreted as if it were actually null.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String defaultValue
      The String representation of the default value to use in case no suitable configuration value may be found.
      String value
      The name of the configuration value in question.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract String value
        The name of the configuration value in question.

        If this element is not specified, the effective configuration value name will be the name of the annotated element upon which this ConfigurationValue appears.

        This element will never return NULL.

        Returns:
        the name of the configuration value in question; never null or NULL
        See Also:
        NULL
        Default:
        ""

      • defaultValue

        public abstract String defaultValue
        The String representation of the default value to use in case no suitable configuration value may be found.

        This element may return NULL.

        Returns:
        the String representation of the default value to use in case no suitable configuration value may be found, or NULL
        See Also:
        NULL
        Default:
        "\u0000"
